        The join() method creates and returns a new string by concatenating all of the elements in an array (or an array-like object), separated by commas or a specified separator string. If the array has only one item, then that item will be returned without using the separator.
        https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/join
        パラメータ:
        s - Specifies a string to separate each pair of adjacent elements of the array. The separator is converted to a string if necessary. If omitted, the array elements are separated with a comma (","). If separator is an empty string, all elements are joined without any characters in between them.
        戻り値:

        If an element is null or an empty array [], it is converted to an empty string.

      • slice

        @NotNull
default @NotNull ICollectionList<V> slice​(int start)
        The slice() method returns a shallow copy of a portion of an array into a new array object selected from start to end (end not included) where start and end represent the index of items in that array. The original array will not be modified. Unlike the JavaScript implementation, the start does not support the negative value. MDN Docs
        パラメータ:
        start - Zero-based index at which to start extraction.
        戻り値:
        A new array containing the extracted elements.

      • slice

        @NotNull
default @NotNull ICollectionList<V> slice​(int start,
                                          int end)
        The slice() method returns a shallow copy of a portion of an array into a new array object selected from start to end (end not included) where start and end represent the index of items in that array. The original array will not be modified. Unlike the JavaScript implementation, the start and the end does not support the negative value. MDN Docs
        パラメータ:
        start - Zero-based index at which to start extraction.
        end - Zero-based index before which to end extraction. slice extracts up to but not including end. For example, slice(1,4) extracts the second element through the fourth element (elements indexed 1, 2, and 3).
        戻り値:
        A new array containing the extracted elements.
